What I Did Today

Revised and practiced all HTML tags learned so far
Built a basic portfolio using pure HTML
Built small mini projects to solidify understanding
Completed HTML fundamentals section


<!DOCTYPE html> — declares HTML5 document
<html> — root element of the page
<head> — contains meta information not visible on page
<body> — contains everything visible to the user
<title> — sets the browser tab title
<meta> — defines charset, viewport, description
Heading Tags

<h1> to <h6> — six levels of headings
<h1> is the most important — only one per page
<h6> is the smallest and least important
Used for structure and SEO — not just for making text big
Text Tags

<p> — paragraph
<span> — inline container for text
<strong> — bold text with importance
<em> — italic text with emphasis
<br> — line break — self closing
<hr> — horizontal line — self closing
<sub> — subscript text below the line
<sup> — superscript text above the line
List Tags

<ul> — unordered list with bullet points
<ol> — ordered list with numbers
<li> — list item used inside both ul and ol
Link and Image Tags

<a href=""> — anchor tag for links
target="_blank" — opens link in new tab
<img src="" alt=""> — displays image — self closing
alt is required for accessibility
Semantic Tags

<header> — top section of page or section
<nav> — navigation links
<main> — main content of the page
<section> — a standalone section of content
<article> — independent self contained content
<aside> — sidebar or related content
<footer> — bottom section of page
Table Tags

<table> — wraps the entire table
<thead> — groups header rows
<tbody> — groups body rows
<tr> — table row
<th> — header cell — bold by default
<td> — data cell
Form Tags

<form> — wraps all form elements
<input> — self closing — many types
<label> — describes an input
<textarea> — multi line text input
<select> — dropdown
<option> — item inside dropdown
<button> — clickable button
Division and Layout Tags

<div> — generic block container
<span> — generic inline container
Other Tags

<title> — browser tab name
<!--comment--> — comment not visible on page
&copy; &amp; &lt; &gt; &nbsp; — HTML entities

Mistakes I Made Today

Used <h1> multiple times on one page — incorrect for SEO
Forgot alt on some images — accessibility issue
Used <div> instead of <section> and <article> — not semantic
Opened a tag but forgot to close it — entire layout broke

How I Fixed Them

Rule: only one <h1> per page — use <h2> and <h3> for subsections
Rule: every image needs alt — no exceptions
Rule: ask myself — does this content have a meaning? Use semantic. Just grouping? Use div
Rule: always close tags immediately after opening before writing content inside
